Time Complexity:

Let n = number of days

    Each index is pushed and popped at most once → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Stack stores indices → O(n)
    Result array → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Approach:

1. Create a stack to store indices of days
   - Stack will maintain decreasing temperatures

2. Traverse array from right to left:

   - While stack is not empty and current temperature ≥ temperature at stack top:
     → pop indices (not useful for next warmer day)

3. After popping:
   - If stack is empty → no warmer day → result[i] = 0
   - Else → result[i] = (index of next warmer day - i)

4. Push current index into stack

5. Continue for all elements

6. Return result array





class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] t) {
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        int result[] = new int[t.length];
        for(int i=t.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(st.size()>0 && t[i] >= t[st.peek()]) st.pop();

            if(st.size()==0) result[i]=0;
            else result[i]=st.peek()-i;

            st.push(i);
        }
        return result;
    }
}
